tip.text: One of my favorite cafe in Kemuning. Food might not all be good but the scrumptious ones are Baked Egg, Salmon Pasta, & Nasi Lemak Goreng for me! 😋 Coffee wise, they're not coffee expert 😕
Tasted authentic, personally feels it suits family/group instead of ala carte for personal.
Food tasted above average, reasonable prices and good services from the crew. 🙂 do call and make reservations, pretty crowded during dinner time!
Everything pork are rather good though. Wide range or variety to pick! It's always crowded tho..
Burgers are better than pastas but not the criss cuts. Price is higher than I expect. Nonetheless, friend staff and cozy environment. Cakes are above average~
Love how they handle the pan seared Salmon. Salted egg yolk duck pasta is way too dry, not to my liking. Hot chocolate is rather mediocre. A cozy place with vintage stuffs.
Another tweak on their Char Hor Fun! Fish were replaced with the "Char Siew" or what u call it. Yums, it would be better to have lesser starch. Just requests 🤗
Limited choice for the lobster's cooking method. Grilled is the best for me, freshness stays. A little pricey thou.. Environment is quite cozy.
Mango spring roll, soufflé, chocolate lava and matcha red bean panna cotta are nice!

venue.name: Happy Together (甜蜜蜜甜品專門店)

tip.text: Beef, egg udon are the bomb! Side dishes are not too bad!
檸檬脆脆、奶油脆脆 all the buns are perfectly done! Scrumptious! Worth the queue and time!
番茄牛肉麵/通心粉最好味！加杯檸檬茶，讚！
Steam custard is the best here! Sandwiches are quite nice too! Worth the queue.

venue.name: Australia Dairy Company (澳洲牛奶公司)

tip.text: Busy environment, nice bar, chili lemon boneless chicken w that generous portion of rocket leaves & avocado is awesome! No complains for big breakfast. Churro is okay but hot chocolate was a turn off

formattedAddress: A-G-1, New Podium, Plaza Vads, 1 Jalan Tun Mohd Faud
location.address: A-G-1, New Podium, Plaza Vads, 1 Jalan Tun Mohd Faud

tip.text: RM5 for this above average steam rice. By looking at all the comments, I have a little high expectations. Overhyped IMO but nonetheless, quite yummy 😉 Btw, is this the right/new name for kak wok?
RM5 for this above average steam rice. By looking at all the comments, I have a little high expectations. Overhyped in my opinion but nonetheless, quite yummy 😉
Minimalist feel, friendly boss and staff. Place is kinda comfy but small. Desserts are all gluten free = fat free 🤗 yums!

location.address: Square Lot C109, Centre Wing, Metropolitan Square, Jalan PJU 8/1, Damansara Perdana.
formattedAddress: Square Lot C109, Centre Wing, Metropolitan Square, Jalan PJU 8/1, Damansara Perdana.

tip.text: 10cents for one Wantan! What else can you ask for?! The soup wantan is scrumptious!!!
Price has increased after a year but doubt not, uncle is still healthy and friendly. Happy to serve, still tasty as it is! 😋
Signature iced coffee is pretty good. Creme brûlée is slightly sweet to my liking, salad is awesome with the amount of rocket salad 😋 baked egg is indifferent from usual ones, wide range of food!
Very cozy environment, outdoor feels so much lively, awesome spot for your foodies shot but bear in mind it's treated as smoking area 😬 so indoor for aircond.
Salmon and salted egg pasta are good but not the not-so-fresh prawns & vege 😕 Cozy environment though. Beeramisu has nothing special, salmon salad was indeed good.
New add on to the menu: "Nasi Briyani Gam Ayam Goreng Perencah"😋
Despite the slight high in price, the Briyani Gam is really good 😍 Mee Bandung & Taufu Bakar are good as well! You pay for the good taste, aye!
Vietnamese coffee tasted awesome, ask the barista to drop a scoop of ice cream into it, it's gonna make your day 😍 Thai Milk Tea is somewhat mediocre 🙂

formattedAddress: The Curve, Jalan PJU 7/3 (The Curve, Damansara)

tip.text: Outdoor seating, best to be here late evening when the sun is not that shinny & hot 🌥

formattedAddress: The Curve, Jalan PJU 7/3 (The Curve, Damansara)

tip.text: Everything tasted good here but speaking about freshness, I guess there're space for improvements 🙂 ventilation is good 😉 Kudos to the live band, they take song requests & soothing voice 🤓
As Hunan style favors savory/hot/sour combination, it's not as hot as Szechuan style 😉 tasty dishes, go for the 水煮魚😋
Matcha & Hojicha are the boom! 😍 both parfait & softserve are scrumptious! Wide range of choices!
Not the typical pork noodle, it's more to sweet. Edible but it just doesn't have the pork noodle feel, pretty much tasteless, even w the pork lard. Curry Chee Cheong Fun is quite a big disappointment
Apparently their wifi is no longer available 😕 but who cares, we are here for Penang food heh! 😋
No longer serving dim sums! Food are all yummy especially the crispy chicken! 🍗 Also, love matching their noodles with the chili oil (similar to HK style). Fried special tofu is scrumptious 😍
Sweet potato fries w secret dip sauce is nice! Duck meat pasta is special but nothing to wow. They have crispy croissants! 😍 scramble egg somewhat doesn't taste good. Egg mayo Bruschetta is the best.
Peanut butter is good, matcha isn't as yummy as I thought, caramel is also okay 😇 they are adding on pastas on menu as time goes by. Cozy environment & wide range of bites to choose 😋
Hirame No Engawa Roast, must try, super yummy but very pricey! 😋 soft shell crab is nice too! Everything on menu looked tasty, just the price. Occasionally visit is fine 😉 Quality food 😊

location.address: OB2.G.U1, Oasis Boulevard, Ground Floor, Sunway Pyramid, No. 3, Jalan PJS 11/15, Bandar Sunway
formattedAddress: OB2.G.U1, Oasis Boulevard, Ground Floor, Sunway Pyramid, No. 3, Jalan PJS 11/15, Bandar Sunway (No. 3, Jalan PJS 11/15)

venue.name: Hana Dining Sake Bar Sdn. Bhd.

tip.text: These 4 dishes are scrumptious! Baked potatoes, baby lobsters, baby squids and pork belly! 😋 squid ink rice is also nice, others are very authentic that only real Spanish would really enjoy maybe 😁
Decent western cuisine around the neighborhood. Fish are all good but nothing special. Mediocre mushroom soup. Pretty much to improve in taste 😉

formattedAddress: G-08 Ground Floor, Gamuda Walk (NoKota Kemuning)

tip.text: Nasi Goreng Daging (beef) won my appetite! If you're a mutton/lamb lover, must not miss them! 😎 colleagues claimed that they are scrumptious!
Food portion is for 2, you might not wanna order one for yourself. Super wide range of choices, mostly tasted good! Teh Tarik terapung is value for money 😅 good place for berbisik-bisik w friends 😂
Wide range of selection, Chinese-Muslim, western! Chinese ones need lotsa improvements! Briyani is nice but pricey, other than that it's quite fine.
Nothing much to wow about the food besides their cute bear presentations. Tasted okay but not to the "I'm coming back again" taste. Guess people are lured by the big bear displays 🐻 desserts are cute
Never ever miss mochatella if you're a Nutella lover 😋 food prices are above average, tasted mediocre but some are special. Don't recommend the messy family drinks, waste of money, doesn't taste good
Good river view, seafood up to standard but not as fresh as they just got caught live. Tasted quite nice, especially the Thai style steam fish, appetizing 😉 mantis is also nice but aren't fleshy.
Signature coconut ice cream! Those who are craving to have the same taste as in Thailand, this is the place! 🌴🍨 any toppings at your favorite! 😍 there's a cafe behind the door, hidden gem!
Both savory and sweet pies are nice! The green tea latte has a very strong greentea aroma 😋 Soda is actually sprite/7up 😅
Place is rather small but cozy. Sometimes you get no place 😕 Mochacino Nutella is nice, red velvet is to my liking! Not too sweet! Their cake is big in size 😃 friendly staffs too!
Cozy environment, friendly boss and good coffee as usual! 😃
Scrumptious cheesecake!😋 mustn't miss if u love cheesecake😍 greentea cake is to my liking as it's not sweet. They serve only tea here 😉 will be back for more cakes! Sitting at the chiller tempting!
Always here for the pork noodle, other than the economical rice, I do not see other stall stay long.

formattedAddress: Jalan Anggerik Vanilla W 31/W, Kota Kemuning
location.address: Jalan Anggerik Vanilla W 31/W, Kota Kemuning

tip.text: Food tasted mediocre, wanton noodles is not as authentic as the ones in Hong Kong, go for the dry one better instead. Dim sums are okay but the fried ones are not hot enough.

formattedAddress: Level 4-16-1, No. 14, Persiaran Anggerik Vanilla (Kota Kemuning)

tip.text: Chocolate brownies & ferrero toast mustn't be missed! 😍 caramel honey toast is scrumptious too! Thai style milk tea is a little sweet compared to Taiwan / Malaysia style 😂 free lemongrass water 👍🏻

formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

venue.name: After You (อาฟเตอร์ ยู)

tip.text: Authentic taste of dim sum! Full of elderly that makes me feel like I'm watching HK dramas 😂 love the 蛋散 and the environment 😍 bird cages brings extra retro feelings!
Best chocolate ever! Must not miss the "super stacked chocolate cake" as the chocolate melts in your mouth, truffles aren't very sweet! JUST GRAB SOMETHING FROM HERE, no regrets for sure! 😍
Set lunch is value for money 😉 love their side dishes, totally different from the normal Korean BBQ joints. Fried chicken is nice, matching w soju 🍶 Bulgogi is yummy! Marinated BBQs are all yummy!
Do a little exercise to get awesome view, it's worth the climb 😉 It's actually better to get express lane when it's crowded. Show at the theater is nice~ carefully manage your time 😇

location.address: Po Lin Monastery, Ngong Ping Rd
formattedAddress: Po Lin Monastery, Ngong Ping Rd

venue.name: Tian Tan Buddha (Giant Buddha) (天壇大佛)

tip.text: Tomato soup base is the boom, fresh meat and ingredients! Place feels a bit outskirt but food is awesome 😋 fried fish skin is crispy & yummy!

venue.name: Old Man Hot Pot (老坑火鍋)

tip.text: I'd say this is a fancy soft serve/cone. Go for honeycomb, Affogato and Caramel if you want something special 😉
Ferraro Rocher is the bomb! It's not very sweet, more to my liking! Flavours rotates every 2 weeks so keep an eye!

location.address: Shop G42, G/F, Miramar Shopping Centre, 132 Nathan Rd
formattedAddress: Shop G42, G/F, Miramar Shopping Centre, 132 Nathan Rd

tip.text: Must try: black sesame pau, har gao, siew mai, & Xiao long pau, mostly all are nice! Operating 24hrs is the main point 😆 my favorite spot for dim sum in HK! Price are reasonable too!

venue.name: King of Dim Sum 點心皇

tip.text: Food here are all scrumptious despite the price that is above average 😋 once in a blue moon is fine! Come w friends if you wanna try lots of them instead of only one choice for yourself.

location.address: Shop 201, 2/F, Causeway Place, 2-10 Great George St
formattedAddress: Shop 201, 2/F, Causeway Place, 2-10 Great George St

tip.text: Brought here by a local friend, cozy environment, food's awesome! Pork shoulder, lobster bisque, French onion soup are nice! Desserts are scrumptious especially the apple tart, advance order needed.

formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

tip.text: Desserts here are scrumptious! You'll literally go "ahh, omg when you have them!" 😍 Matcha Molten Cake is the best! (For green tea lover). The caramel banana waffle is also awesome! 😋

location.address: Shop 201, 2/F, Causeway Place, 2-10 Great George St
formattedAddress: Shop 201, 2/F, Causeway Place, 2-10 Great George St

tip.text: Love grabbing the free coffee with the Waitrose card from the cafe and their soup taste good! 😋 spacious car park and great departmental management.
Iconic spot for tourist, don't forget to visit the National Gallery! It's pretty interesting inside, plus, that's the place for loo 🙈 (if you need)
Enjoy the nature here, with the squirrels, ducks, goose etc! 😆 You could also see London Eye from certain spot! I bet people love jogging & picnic here, renting the docks! 😉
Always love this place, visited a few times. ☺️ Be there as early before 11am to see the changing of guards, grab a good spot for photos, especially the blooming flowers during spring! 🌻🌷🌼
Burgers are scrumptious, onion rings are gigantic & yummy! Not to mention their milkshakes, mustn't miss them especially Oreo 😍
Not sure if I'm a tourist or the guy is nice. I get to try all the sauce FOC! Kudos! Thanks and they all tasted awesome 😉
Back here again after a year. Roti canai used to be good but now it tasted different especially the dhal. Tom yam Mee Hun Kuey is something special but just for a bite or two, after that hmm..
"German technology, made in Malaysia" A. & H. Meyer is a fully customize in manufacturing power socket outlets, leader in cable management system. For more info, kindly visit www.ah-meyer.com.my

formattedAddress: No. 3, Jalan Astaka U8/84 (Section U8, Bukit Jelutong)

tip.text: Pork noodle is the bomb here either in soup or dry 😍 Not to forget their awesome curry noodles!
Wide range of food menu, combination of western & Japanese 😃 taste above average, spicy capsicum sauce for grilled/fried chicken is special 😋 special duck meat sushi rolls & coffee cube matcha is 👍
Authentic Sze Chuan food! Basically everything here is more to spicy, that's Sze Chuan style isn't it?😉 Friendly lady boss, make reservations if you plan to come after 1915hr, pretty pack on weekends

location.address: No.8 Jalan Anggerik Vanilla 31/BE Kota Kemuning
formattedAddress: No.8 Jalan Anggerik Vanilla 31/BE Kota Kemuning

tip.text: Always have a thing towards their desserts, for years! I wouldn't miss the mushroom soup on every visit, like A MUST! Recent new dessert is awesome, especially the Cookie Monster 😍 GO FOR IT!

formattedAddress: 32-1, The Strand, Jalan PJU 5/20D, Kota Damansara
location.address: 32-1, The Strand, Jalan PJU 5/20D, Kota Damansara

tip.text: Used to be at the Wong Soon Kee coffee shop at SS14, now they are here on their own, food still awesome as usual! Fried chicken is the best! 😍

formattedAddress: No 26 (Jalan Jurureka U1/40, Seksyen U1, Hicom Glenmarie)
location.crossStreet: Jalan Jurureka U1/40, Seksyen U1, Hicom Glenmarie

tip.text: Love the cozy ambience and comfortable lightings environment. Didn't get to try the cooked food, but desserts & drinks were all good! Will be back on next trip! Ice cream puff coated w chocolate 👍🏻
Hershey's Chocolate Cake + Ice Cream is a must if you're looking for dessert! Best ahhh~ the boom :)
